title: APC NetShelter PDU: Power and Current
agents: snmp
catalog: hw/power/apc
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the electrical current, power consumption, and total load
 of APC NetShelter Advanced Rack PDU units (APDU series, OID subtree .318.1.1.32).

 At the device level it reports total power consumption and load as a percentage
 of rated capacity (default thresholds: {WARN} at 80%, {CRIT} at 90%).

 At the phase level it reports current draw and power. The device provides
 current thresholds which are applied automatically. If a threshold is
 exceeded the service goes {WARN} or {CRIT}.

 At the bank level it reports current draw.

 Thresholds can be overridden using the "Parameters for input phases of
 UPSs and PDUs" ruleset.

item:
 The device name, phase number, or bank name

discovery:
 One service is created for the device, one for each phase, and one for each bank
